33 SECTION 2. Section 10 of Chapter 70B of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
34 Official Edition, is hereby amended by adding the following new subsection:
35 (d) Notwithstanding any state law, state regulation, or agency policy to the contrary, the
36 authority shall be authorized and directed to add twenty (20) percentage points to the project
37 reimbursement rates for regional vocational-technical high school and county, regional and
38 independent agricultural high school construction so that reimbursement rates for such projects
39 are not less than 75% nor more than 90% of the eligible costs. Further, the authority shall add
40 five (5) percentage points to the reimbursement rate for any project that includes state-approved
41 vocational-technical education programs as defined in Chapter 74 of the General Laws aligned
42 with priorities specifically identified in the Regional Labor Market Blueprint for the region in
43 which the school is located. However, additional percentage points shall not be awarded unless
44 the school currently offers five (5) or more Chapter 74 programs. In no case shall the total
45 reimbursement for a project exceed 90% of eligible costs.
46 SECTION 3. Chapter 69 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition,
47 is hereby amended by adding the following sections:-
48 Section 38. For the purposes of sections 38 and 39, inclusive, the following terms shall
49 have the following meanings, unless the context clearly requires otherwise:-
50 “District of residence”, shall mean the school district of the city or town where a student
51 resides.
