52 “School of residence”, shall mean the middle school or junior high school a student
53 attends within their district of residence.
54 Section 39. (a) The department of elementary and secondary education shall develop and
55 implement policies and promulgate regulations to promote, enhance, and expand vocational-
56 technical education programs, as defined in Chapter 74 of the General Laws, in the
57 commonwealth.
58 (b) The department shall:
59 (i) oversee all Chapter 74 approved programs and ensure compliance with M.G.L.
60 Chapter 74 and related regulations;
61 (ii) work to increase awareness of vocational-technical education and career opportunities
62 among students in elementary schools, junior high schools, and middle schools;
63 (iii) ensure that schools offering Chapter 74 programs are provided reasonable access
64 during the school day at schools of residence to meet with all students and distribute information
65 about vocational-technical education and careers to said students, including English language
66 learners, students with disabilities, students of color, and other student populations, to ensure that
67 such information is provided equitably to all learners;
68 (iv) ensure that schools offering Chapter 74 programs are given the opportunity during
69 the school day to host middle school tours, with transportation costs paid by the school hosting
70 the tour, for all middle school students in member communities, including English language
71 learners, students with disabilities, students of color, and other student populations to ensure that
72 such opportunities are provided equitably to all learners; and further ensure that the school of
